Step 1. Loading data

The first step will be creating a folder for the project and sub folders for applications, resources and others



     then create the following sub folders




      The next step will be collecting the source data to the resource folder from  the website.


After having all data sources  we can create the document  from qlik sense or qlik view

For this project qlik sense will be used.

Open the qlik sense app then   click create new app button


and name it Chicago_Crime_2001-present then hit create



After the new app is created open the app.

Then select script editor to load data (we have two options to load data  ,with script editor or data manager)


From the script editor create the data connection by clicking the create new connection button at the top right corner




Then select All files under file locations



Then select the path for the data source and give the connection name as ‘Chicago_crime_data_source_connection’ then click ‘ Create button’.

Then you can see the connection created


 

then click the folder icon to bring the connection to select the file  and click select





Then you will see the columns of the data.  uncheck fields to remove from your data set , select the file type as delimited ,file names as embedded field names, comma delimiter

Finally click insert script to insert the script to the script editor




then you will  load statement in script editor


Here in order to make data loading efficient and to handle incremental loading we should create QVD file, and variable to catch last update date. In order to create the Qvd file we can use STORE key word and the file connection name and QVD file name with qvd extension. One more thing here, name the prior table as ‘crime’ in the script editor.



Now click load data button on the top right corner to load the data to the qlik memory


Now we can see the qvd file is created


in order to use the qvd file we a new connection should be created  (use the same step used above to create  Chicago_crime_data_source_connection) and we use the qvd file  as a source of data .




follow the following steps to load the qvd file 



once the field are selected click  insert script 


Then load the data and move to Analysis section to create the dashboards
